#: src/pages/docs/concepts/GlossaryPage.tsx:244
msgid "A named, atomically applied recall of multiview state: one salvo can switch the layout, rebind sources into cells, and update tally and labels in a single action. Borrowed from router control, where a salvo fires many crosspoint takes at once."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:209
msgid "A per-cell <0>qos</0> block sets a degradation <1>priority</1> and strategy, so the engine sheds the cheapest tiles first under load before touching the program output."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/ProbesPage.tsx:487
msgid "A probe watches one cell for a fail state and raises an alarm after its dwell window."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/SourcesPage.tsx:431
msgid "A reference only — never a plaintext secret. Leave blank for none."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/SalvosPage.tsx:92
msgid "A salvo id is required"
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/FeaturesPage.tsx:139
msgid "A salvo is a named, atomically-applied recall. One salvo can switch the layout, rebind sources into cells, set tally colors, and update under-monitor display text — all at once — so an operator can move a whole arrangement (say, a VTR review setup) with a single action instead of a series of separate edits."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/concepts/GlossaryPage.tsx:101
msgid "A small receive-side buffer that absorbs the uneven arrival of network packets so frames can be consumed smoothly. Deeper buffers ride out worse networks but add latency. Each Multiview input has its own bounded buffering; an overflowing input drops its oldest data rather than growing without limit."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ComposePage.tsx:39
msgid "A small RTSP server that, on start, runs ffmpeg to publish a synthetic test pattern with a sine-wave audio tone to <0>rtsp://testsrc:8554/test</0>."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/concepts/CodecsPage.tsx:121
msgid "A software fallback always exists, so a build without any GPU still works — just with less headroom."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/SimplePages.tsx:679
#~ msgid "A solid source needs a hex colour like #101014 or #abc."
#~ msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/FeaturesPage.tsx:40
msgid "A source is a managed input. Each one owns its ingest, decode, color handling, and reconnect behaviour, and is referenced by tiles via a stable id. Supported kinds include RTSP, HLS, MPEG-TS, SRT, RTMP, NDI, file, and a built-in synthetic test pattern. When a source stops delivering frames, its tile holds the last good frame and moves through a clear state machine — live, stale, reconnecting, no-signal — while the engine reconnects without disturbing the rest of the wall."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/SourcesPage.tsx:519
msgid "A source is an ingest input bound into the multiview by id."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/SimplePages.tsx:1120
#~ msgid "A target is required."
#~ msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/concepts/GlossaryPage.tsx:221
msgid "A TCP push protocol that remains the most widely accepted way to send a live stream to a platform. Classic RTMP carries H.264 and AAC only; enhanced endpoints negotiate newer codecs. Latency is typically a few seconds."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ComposePage.tsx:53
msgid "A tiny nginx that serves the HLS volume over HTTP so you can open the stream in a player at <0>http://[::1]:8888/multiview.m3u8</0>."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ComposePage.tsx:53
#~ msgid "A tiny nginx that serves the HLS volume over HTTP so you can open the stream in a player at <0>http://localhost:8888/multiview.m3u8</0>."
